## Expected Behavior

When multiple allowedOwners are in the template, the user selects the desired owner and the selection remains while filling out the rest of the template form.

## Actual Behavior

When multiple allowedOwners exist, the user has to select the desired owner twice to get the selection to "stick", and also the selection switches back to the first option when the "Repository" field is updated.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Use a template with RepoUrlPicker containing multiple allowedOwners
    ```
    - title: Choose a location
      required:
        - repoUrl
      properties:
        repoUrl:
          title: Repository Location
          type: string
          ui:field: RepoUrlPicker
          ui:options:
            allowedHosts:
              - github.com
            allowedOwners:
              - some-github-owner-A
              - some-github-owner-B
              - some-github-owner-C
            requestUserCredentials:
              secretsKey: USER_OAUTH_TOKEN
    ```
2. Select an owner (B) other than the first (A), it should remain on the first (A)
3. Select owner (B) again, it should now remain selected (B)
4. Start typing in the Repository field, the owner should switch back to the first (A)

## Context

We're trying to limit the owners available to the user by presenting a list of GitHub organizations to choose from.

This results in difficulty for the user to select their owner, they have to select the owner multiple times to get it to "stick" when filling out the template forms, or they don't see the owner switch on them and end up creating the repository in the wrong organization.

## Your Environment

This behaviour happens in Safari and Firefox, though I mainly work in Safari.

